# Rust / Tauri
src-tauri/target/
src-tauri/gen/

# Lockfiles — intentionally untracked. This is single-build-machine, CEO-operated
# tooling, so dependency-pin churn from a local build must never surface as a
# reviewable (accidentally-committable) change. Manifests stay tracked — Cargo.toml
# and package.json are the build's source of truth; only the generated locks are
# ignored. (Trade-off: cross-machine build reproducibility is not pinned. Acceptable
# for one builder; commit a lock if a second build host is ever added.)
Cargo.lock
package-lock.json

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
*.log
.idea/
.vscode/
